Down Bad, Down-Ballot

It didn=E2=80=99t take long for some House members to conclude that the ris=
ks outweigh the rewards of embracing the historic, headline-grabbing, fundr=
aising-record-breaking Harris candidacy. Earlier today, six House Democrats=
 resolutely distanced themselves from their party=E2=80=99s presumptive nom=
inee and joined with the entire House Republican caucus to pass a 220-196 m=
easure =E2=80=9Cstrongly condemning the Biden Administration and its Border=
 Czar, Kamala Harris=E2=80=99s, failure to secure the United States border.=
=E2=80=9D

The startling defection offers a window into the anxieties felt by Democrat=
s locked in close down-ballot races. Of the six members to sign the measure=
, five are embattled so-called frontliners: Don Davis (North Carolina), Yad=
ira Caraveo (Colorado), Jared Golden (Maine), Mary Peltola (Alaska), and Ma=
rie
Gluesenkamp Perez (Washington). The sixth member, Texas=E2=80=99s Henry Cue=
llar, represents a border district and could also be in electoral trouble. =
(Cuellar, if you recall, is currently under indictment, along with his wife=
, for allegedly accepting $600,000 in bribes from Azerbaijan.)

At the moment, it remains unclear how Harris will play in certain districts=
 versus others. The very, very early read on Harris is that she is performi=
ng better than Biden in national polling, but it will take at least a week=
=E2=80=94if not longer=E2=80=94before benchmark polling of Harris in compet=
itive districts comes back to candidates and incumbents. Nonetheless, it=E2=
=80=99s both striking and telling that these Democratic members chose to ro=
w upstream against the surge of enthusiasm and unprecedented fundraising.

When the House returns from August recess, these members=E2=80=99 anxieties=
 will likely be compounded by the annual September spending battle ahead of=
 the new fiscal year
on October 1, which brings with it the almost inevitable threat of a govern=
ment shutdown deep into election season. When I raised this topic with a se=
nior Democratic aide on the Hill, they texted back, =E2=80=9Clol I don=E2=
